        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 3:41PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 341 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles northeast of Greenbank, moving northeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bartow.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
